Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Scrotum, trauma' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Discontinuity of tunica albuginea' radio button is enabled
And 'Intact tunica albuginea' radio button is enabled

And 'Hematocele' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled

And 'Testicular capsule rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Testicular contusion' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Discontinuity of tunica albuginea' radio button
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Hematoma' checkbox
Then 'Scrotal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vas deferens' checkbox is enabled
And 'Non-displacing' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Testicular capsule rupture' radio button
Then 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Testicular contusion' radio button
Then 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled
